description:
This is a 21 minute workout called '20 Min ABS WORKOUT at Home [NO EQUIPMENT + NO REPEAT] Caroline Girvan' from the channel Caroline Girvan.
The workout falls under Strength/Body weight and Cardio/Mat.
It's suitable for Intermediate and Beginner fitness levels.
The workout has a The Meditative Grind and The Foundation Builder vibe.
The technique difficulty is Intermediate and Beginner.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: No equipment needed for this 20 minute at home abs workout. I do love some stretching and some extra ab work on my active rest days so I thought I would record this simple routine for you to save for those low impact days when you want to move but not affect your training the next day!

These movements are all different each performed for 50 seconds, 10 seconds brief rest. This is a slow paced routine to really encourage that extra focus on lower back flat on mat and core braced throughout.

Just grab your mat and join me for a 20 minute ab routine, targeting the lower abs, upper abs, obliques and entire core!

PLANK TWIST
PLANK ALT KNEE SIDE TUCK
DEAD BUG
TOE TAPS
ELBOWS ALT TUCK TO EXT
REACH TO LEG LOWER
STRAIGHT LEG REVERSE CRUNCH
HIP LIFT
LEG LOWER TO FROG TUCK
TABLE TOP SINGLE LEG EXT
TABLE TOP SINGLE LEG EXT (switch)
OPP HAND TO FOOT CHOP
OPP HAND TO FOOT CHOP (switch)
HIP LIFT TO ALT TWIST
CRUNCH WITH PULSE
OPP ELBOW TO KNEE CRUNCH
OPP ELBOW TO KNEE CRUNCH (switch)
HUG TO HOLLOW...
